      • contains

        public static <T> boolean contains(T obj,
                                   T... objs)
        Whether or not the specified object is in the specified array. This method does use the equals() method to test for the presence of the object. Seem could be achieved using Arrays.asList(objs).contains(obj). However this method return as soon as a match is found, so is somewhat faster with large arrays.
        Parameters:
        obj - The object
        objs - The array
        Returns:
        Whether or not the specified object is in the specified array.
        See Also:
        in(Object, Object...)

                             Object... options)
